title.narrative: Accelerating HIV and AIDS, Tuberculosis Prevention, Treatment, Care and Support and building resilient and sustainable systems for health in The Gambia

description.narrative: Gambia - TB/HIV - The National AIDS Secretariat of the Republic of The Gambia - NAS. This program has the following goals: To accelerate achievement of the 90-90-90 targets in line with our national, regional and global commitments in 2025, from 43%, 68%, 19% in 2019. To reduce the TB incidence rate from 174/100,000 population in 2018 to 139/100,000 population by the end of 2022. The objectives of this program are: Increase the proportion of PLHIV who know their status from 43% in 2019 to 90% by 2025. Increase the proportion of PLHIV on treatment from 68% in 2019 to 90% by 2025. Increase the proportion of PLHIV on treatment who are virally supressed from 19% in 2019 to 90% by 2025. Ensure Zero stigma and discrimination and enhance the human rights of PLHIV. Facilitate a Sustainable National Response to HIV and AIDS. Improved identification, treatment and management of co-infections from 61% in 2017 to 100% 2022. To detect at least 95% of all TB Patients within 1-2 weeks of the onset of symptoms by 2022 from 65% in 2017. To achieve and sustain a treatment success rate of at least 95% by 2022 from a baseline of 88% in 2015 for all new patients. To increase the proportion of HIV testing among TB patients from 88% in 2017 to 100% by 2022. To increase the proportion of children under 15 with TB notified to the NLTP from the current 6% (2017) to 10% by 2022
